Package com.example.cs213_tuition_project_javafx

Class Roster

java.lang.Object
com.example.cs213_tuition_project_javafx.Roster
public class Roster extends Object
Roster Data Structure that holds Student Objects. Ability to add and remove student from our DS. Check if our DS is empty. Expand the size of our DS as we add more elements As well as sorting methods and printing methods for our Roster DS.

      Check to see if a particular student is in the roster. If so, change the major of that student.
      Parameters:
      student - student that we want to change the major of.
      newMajor - the major we need to change to.
      Returns:
      true if major changed successfully, false if student not found.

    • updateCreditsCompleted

      public void updateCreditsCompleted(Enrollment enrollment)
      Updates the creditCompleted data in Student object by taking the creditsEnrolled value and adding it to creditsCompleted.
      Parameters:
      enrollment - list of enrolled students that have finished the semester. We use this list to get the number of credits each student has completed this semester.

    • rosterMajorSort

      private void rosterMajorSort(Student[] roster)

      Parameters:
      roster - array of student objects to be sorted.

    • printByStanding

      Prints the sorted roster (sorted by standing).

    • rosterStandingSort

      private void rosterStandingSort(Student[] roster)
      Sorts roster by standing. The comparable in this method, is the (String) grade of the student Ex:"Freshman".
      Parameters:
      roster - array of student objects to be sorted.

    • filterBySchool

      public boolean filterBySchool(String school, Roster newRoster)
      * Filters our roster by school. Checks to see if the school is valid school at our university. Then goes through our main roster and adds students to a new roster, If their majors match the input school.
      Parameters:
      school - school to filter roster by.
      newRoster - empty roster we will add students too if they are part of a particular school.
      Returns:
      true if school is valid, false otherwise.

    • containsPositive

      private boolean containsPositive(int[] compareables)
      Checks to see if array has any positive values. If there is a positive value, it means that there exists two elements, such that element i is greater than element i+1 in our roster.
      Parameters:
      compareables - array of values of comparisons between elements.
      Returns:
      true if contains positive number, false otherwise.
